* {{IPA|/es.peˈran.to/|lang=eo}}, {{SAMPA|/es pe"ran to/}}

===Etymology===
From the verb {{term|esperi||to hope|lang=eo}}, which derives from {{etyl|la|eo}} {{term|sperare||to hope|lang=la}}, and the affix [[-anto]]; meaning in Esperanto ''one who hopes''.  ''Doktoro Esperanto'' ("Doctor Hopeful") was the pen-name of Esperanto's author, Dr. Zamenhof, when he published the language in 1887.

